Rate all following items on a 5 point scale from "strongly believe that is wrong" (1) to "strongly believe that it is not wrong" (5).



For example, if you considered the statement "Drinking a can of soda in a store without paying for it" as morally wrong behavior, you could rate the statement a '1'. - Using VPNs or proxies to bypass geographical restrictions.
Q3_honest_reviews:
Rate all following items on a 5 point scale from "strongly believe that is wrong" (1) to "strongly believe that it is not wrong" (5).



For example, if you considered the statement "Drinking a can of soda in a store without paying for it" as morally wrong behavior, you could rate the statement a '1'. - Taking time to write thorough, honest reviews for small online businesses, especially when they provide good service.
Q4_company-license:
Rate all following items on a 5 point scale from "strongly believe that is wrong" (1) to "strongly believe that it is not wrong" (5).



For example, if you considered the statement "Drinking a can of soda in a store without paying for it" as morally wrong behavior, you could rate the statement a '1'. - Continuing to use company-licensed software after employment termination, despite knowing access should have been revoked.
Q5_status:
Rate all following items on a 5 point scale from "strongly believe that is wrong" (1) to "strongly believe that it is not wrong" (5).



For example, if you considered the statement "Drinking a can of soda in a store without paying for it" as morally wrong behavior, you could rate the statement a '1'. - Falsely claiming or misrepresenting current status (e.g. student/professional/family member) to maintain access to restricted discounts or services.
Q6_screenshots: Rate the following items on a 5 point scale from "strongly believe that is wrong" (1) to "strongly believe that it is not wrong" (5). - Taking screenshots/recordings of paid content and sharing them with others to help them avoid paying.
Q7_bots: Rate the following items on a 5 point scale from "strongly believe that is wrong" (1) to "strongly believe that it is not wrong" (5). - Using bots & automated tools to purchase limited edition items before human buyers can, with the intent to resell.
Q8_streaming: Rate the following items on a 5 point scale from "strongly believe that is wrong" (1) to "strongly believe that it is not wrong" (5). - Using illegal streaming websites to watch content without paying.
Q9_loyalty: Rate the following items on a 5 point scale from "strongly believe that is wrong" (1) to "strongly believe that it is not wrong" (5). - Using someone else's loyalty card or account to gain points or discounts.
Q10_return: Rate the following items on a 5 point scale from "strongly believe that is wrong" (1) to "strongly believe that it is not wrong" (5). - Deliberately ordering items with the intention to use them temporarily and return them.
Q11_VPN_prices: Rate the following items on a 5 point scale from "strongly believe that is wrong" (1) to "strongly believe that it is not wrong" (5). - Using VPNs to misrepresent one’s location in order to purchase digital products at lower prices meant for other regions.
Q12_free_trials: Rate the following items on a 5 point scale from "strongly believe that is wrong" (1) to "strongly believe that it is not wrong" (5). - Repeatedly accessing free trials intended for first-time users by creating multiple accounts.
Q13_not_reporting: Rate the following items on a 5 point scale from "strongly believe that is wrong" (1) to "strongly believe that it is not wrong" (5). - Discovering an online seller distributing counterfeit products as authentic and not reporting it.
Q14_subscritpion: Rate the following items on a 5 point scale from "strongly believe that is wrong" (1) to "strongly believe that it is not wrong" (5). - Sharing subscription service login credentials with others, in violation of terms of use.
Q15_fake_review: Rate the following items on a 5 point scale from "strongly believe that is wrong" (1) to "strongly believe that it is not wrong" (5). - Writing fake positive reviews in exchange for compensation from the sellers.
Q16_ad-blockers: Rate the following items on a 5 point scale from "strongly believe that is wrong" (1) to "strongly believe that it is not wrong" (5). - Using ad-blockers on free websites that entirely rely on advertising revenue.
Q17_website_errors: Rate the following items on a 5 point scale from "strongly believe that is wrong" (1) to "strongly believe that it is not wrong" (5). - Reporting website pricing errors or security vulnerabilities to online retailers instead of taking advantage of them.
